frameDefinitions: An Agent acts in such a way as to give the incorrect impression to observers that a particular State_of_affairs holds.
In this frame, an Agent changes the temperature of an Item.
A Dodger acts to avoid an oncoming moving Bad_entity.
An Agent causes a Hidden_object to become perceptually inaccessible to potential perceivers by placing it in a Hiding_place or putting in place an Obstruction that screens the object.
A  Counter_actor or Cause  impedes an Agent in an Activity or impedes the unfolding or continuation of a State_of_affairs.
An Obstruction blocks an Eclipsed entity partially or completely from view.
frameExamples: Jordan <t>feigned</t> a love of jazz music to get her phone number .
Margaret Anne <t>chilled</t> the salad to 30 degrees.
Mo <t>dodged</t>  the flower pot that Larry threw in disgust.
Therefore, as I passed the school, I <t>hid</t> the gun and holster in the mailbox

However, as this story goes on the Queen of Sodom has a brother who
plans to <t>undermine</t> his sister and take the throne of Sodom.
A small green bulb <t>concealed</t> behind the panel flashed on momentarily .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who acts in a misleading way to create the impression that a <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> holds.
This is the entity which is copied. With verbs it is frequently expressed as an NP Object: Pat <t>falsified</t> <fex name='Original'>the papers</fex>.
The Copy produced by the Creator most commonly occurs as the External Argument of a predicative use of an adjective or noun target: <fex name='Copy'>The painting</fex> is a <t>fake</t>.
The <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is a an event, a state, or a property that the <fen>Agent</fen> wants others to believe have occurred or hold.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> feigns something.
The place in which the <fen>Agent</fen> feigns something.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs the intentional act which changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The <fen>Item</fen> undergoes the temperature change.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that changes the temperature. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
The <fen>Hot_Cold_source</fen> is the source of the heat or coolness.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where  the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the temperature of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The <fen>Dodger</fen> acts to avoid an oncoming <fen>Bad_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Bad_entity</fen> is  the oncoming entity to avoid.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> at which the dodging occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the dodging occurs.
The <fen>Hidden_object</fen> is the entity which is blocked from view.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who causes the Hidden_entity to be not perceptually accessible to potential perceivers.
The location in which the <fen>Hidden_object</fen> is placed so as not to be perceptually accessible.
<fen>Time</fen> denotes the interval of time during which the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Hidden_object</fen> to become hidden from perceptual access.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the spatial setting in which the hiding event takes place.
An event or state_of_Affairs that successfully impedes an <fen>Agent</fen> or a State_of_affairs.
A person who intentionally or not acts in such a way that an <fen>Agent</fen> or State_of_affairs is impeded.
A person who is intentionally engaged in some <fen>Activity</fen> and who is impeded in that <fen>Activity</fen>.
An <fen>Activity</fen> that is being impeded.
A state or event that is ongoing and whose continuance or unfolding is impeded.
The time at which the <fen>Counter_actor</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> works agains the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Counter_actor</fen> subverts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
The entity which blocks the <fen>Eclipsed</fen> entity from view.
The entity which is blocked from view.

Ryan reheated <fex>the pasta</fex> in the microwave.

Mo dodged <fex> the flower pot that Larry threw in disgust</fex>.
